ar larger share of the federal budget than its current meager 0.4 percent.</=
p>
<p>NASA has <a href=3D"http://www.scientificamerican.com/article/a-waste-of-=
space-commentary/">no plans</a> for a large, spinning cycler spacecraft betw=
een Earth and Mars, probably because such a spacecraft is considered unaffor=
dable. In fact, ongoing squabbles in Washington over how to divvy up NASA=E2=
